        <div class="row-dotted-line"></div>

        <h3>2. Selecting the correct extension</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>You should now be on the home page of the chrome web strore. On the the top left you'll see a search bar, in it type uBlock Origin. 
            You'll get a list of mixed results, make sure to select the one with the name spelled exactly as uBlock Origin and the emblem matches the one in the picture below.</li>
            <li>Now that you've selected the correct extension, your current page should look similar to the one in the picture below. <strong>It is important that the extension is offered by Raymond Hill</strong>. 
            You'll verify that by looking under Additional information on the page, I added paranthesis around it on the picture below.</li>
            <li>All that's left to do is click the blue add to chrome button on top right.</li>
        </ul>

